{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. While crimes of this nature warrant a strict penalty to deter similar behavior, several mitigating factors have been taken into account under the sentencing guidelines. The defendant has no prior criminal record, demonstrating that this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already begun making restitution by partially paying back the stolen funds, showing remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Balancing the need for punitive deterrence with the defendant's mitigating circumstances, a brief period of actual incarceration is appropriate. This sentence is intended to be served prior to a probationary period during which the remaining restitution must be paid in full.",
  "verdict": 6
}
